{
  "prob_desc_input_spec": "The first line of the input contains two integers $$$n$$$, $$$k$$$ ($$$1 \\le n, k \\le 10^{14}$$$) — the number of toys and the expected total cost of the pair of toys.",
  "prob_desc_notes": "NoteIn the first example Tanechka can choose the pair of toys ($$$1, 4$$$) or the pair of toys ($$$2, 3$$$).In the second example Tanechka can choose only the pair of toys ($$$7, 8$$$).In the third example choosing any pair of toys will lead to the total cost less than $$$20$$$. So the answer is 0.In the fourth example she can choose the following pairs: $$$(1, 1000000000000)$$$, $$$(2, 999999999999)$$$, $$$(3, 999999999998)$$$, ..., $$$(500000000000, 500000000001)$$$. The number of such pairs is exactly $$$500000000000$$$.",
