  "prob_desc_output_spec": "Print the number of ways to choose the pair of toys satisfying the condition above. Print 0, if Tanechka can choose no pair of toys in such a way that their total cost is $$$k$$$ burles.",
  "source_code": "#include <stdio.h>\n\nint main(void) {\n\t// your code goes here\n\tunsigned long long int n,k;\n\tscanf(\"%llu %llu\",&n,&k);\n\t\n\tif(n>=k)\n\t    printf(\"%llu\\n\",(k-1)/2);\n\telse{\n\t    if(2*n<=k)\n\t        printf(\"0\\n\");\n\t    else{\n\t        if(n%2==0 && k%2==0)\n\t            printf(\"%llu\\n\",((2*n)-k)/2);\n\t        else\n\t            printf(\"%llu\\n\",((2*n)-k+1)/2);\n\t    }\n\t}\n\treturn 0;\n}\n\n",
